<div type="definition">
<p>VIRTUE of MORAL APPROPRIATENESS, AND CONFORMITY to the LAW.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The standard word for rectitude and justice is yì 義 "what is right and proper".</p>
<p>2. Lǐ 理 may perhaps be taken to be the principle which justifies what is right and proper.</p>
<p>3. Dào 道 can be taken to refer to the way of behaviour that conforms to what is right and proper.</p>
<p>4. Gōng 公 (ant. piān 偏 ) refers to public-spirited and evenhanded justice, and sometimes this virtue is referred to by the binome gōng píng 公平.</p>
        </div>
<div type="modern-chinese-criteria">
